<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-53-0824 </DOCNO><TEXT>The charts of 25 pediatric patients with brain stem tumors have been reviewed.The use of computed tomography was found to have been valuable in diagnosisand follow-up, as well as in the design of radiation therapy portals.Radiotherapy and combination chemotherapy with VM-26 (4'-1 demethyl-epipodophyllotoxin B-D-thenylidene glucoside) and CCNU(1-2-chloroethyl-methyl-3-Cyclohexyl-1-nitrosourea)were the treatment employed. (M.A.C.).</TEXT></DOC>